                            Kurdistan has seen significant development in tourism infrastructure. Major cities like <strong>HewlÃªr (Erbil)</strong>, <strong>SilÃªmanÃ® (Sulaymaniyah)</strong>, and <strong>Duhok</strong> now have international hotels alongside traditional guesthouses. The <strong>Erbil Citadel</strong>, one of the oldest continuously inhabited settlements, attracts many visitors. Hotels range from luxury five-star establishments to budget-friendly options, but Kurdish hospitality remains a constant - staff often go above and beyond to make guests feel welcome.
