                        <p style="line-height: 1.8;">
                            Kurdistan offers diverse tourism experiences. Mountain resorts in areas like <strong>Amadiya</strong> and <strong>Rawanduz</strong> attract visitors seeking nature and cooler climates. The <strong>Gali Ali Beg</strong> waterfall and <strong>Bekhal</strong> waterfall are popular destinations. Historical sites include ancient churches, mosques, and archaeological sites. Eco-tourism and adventure tourism (hiking, skiing, rock climbing) are growing sectors. Hotels and guesthouses in these areas often feature traditional Kurdish architecture and cuisine.
                        </p>
