                        <p style="line-height: 1.8;">
                            Hotel breakfasts in Kurdistan typically include both international and traditional Kurdish items. You'll find <strong>nan</strong> (fresh bread), <strong>penÃ®r</strong> (white cheese), <strong>hingiv</strong> (honey), <strong>rÃ»n</strong> (butter), <strong>hÃªk</strong> (eggs prepared various ways), <strong>zeytÃ»n</strong> (olives), and fresh vegetables. Kurdish breakfast also features <strong>qeymaq</strong> (clotted cream) with honey, and plenty of hot <strong>Ã§ay</strong> (tea). This generous breakfast reflects the Kurdish value of starting the day well-fed and energized.
